description.narrative:
This project will support the Secretary-General to build consensus amongst member countries, thereby determining and advancing the strategic objectives of the Commonwealth and promoting its values and principles. It will achieve this primarily through advance preparation for the Commonwealth Heads of Government Meeting (CHOGM) and the delivery of Commonwealth Foreign Affairs Ministers’ Meeting (CFAMM) held in the margins of the UN General Assembly. This project will also promote Commonwealth interests through its engagement with regional, sub-regional, and other international organisations, primarily the United Nations (UN), African Union (AU), Caribbean Community (CARICOM), European Union (EU) and Pacific Islands Forum (PIF).
This project will enable the Secretary-General to build consensus within the Commonwealth on emerging and contentious issues affecting its members, including territorial disputes (for example, through the Commonwealth Ministerial Group on Guyana and the Commonwealth Ministerial Committee on Belize), and in the consideration of new membership to the Commonwealth (such as Zimbabwe, this includes immediate follow-up engagement post-membership such as The Gambia).
